[
  "James Goodnight cofounded the analytics software firm SAS in 1976 with John Sall, whom he met while a PhD student at North Carolina State University.",
  "Goodnight has been at the helm since the company's inception, when it developed software to analyze agricultural data.",
  "SAS products are used by more than 83,000 organizations around the world; revenues in 2020 were $3 billion.",
  "Goodnight and Sall, who is also a billionaire, founded private school Cary Academy together and co-own a country club and a hotel."
